.SH NAME
netdev_rx_handler_register \- register receive handler
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" netdev_rx_handler_register
.BI "(struct net_device *dev "  ","
.BI "rx_handler_func_t *rx_handler "  ","
.BI "void *rx_handler_data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device to register a handler for
.IP "rx_handler" 12
receive handler to register
.IP "rx_handler_data" 12
data pointer that is used by rx handler

Register a receive handler for a device. This handler will then be
called from __netif_receive_skb. A negative errno code is returned
on a failure.

The caller must hold the rtnl_mutex.

For a general description of rx_handler, see enum rx_handler_result.
